@endnode

@node GAD_QUIT
    Name:  Quit Gadget

 Purpose:  To Quit/Exit the program.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "Q"
@endnode

@node GAD_GP
    Name:  General Practitioner (G.P.) Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows you to optimize your disks and partitions for maximum
           system performance.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing
           this operation.

Keyboard:  "G"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANTISEPTIC
    Name:  Antiseptic Gadget

 Purpose:  To wipe Drive or Free Space of ALL data.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing
           this operation.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_DISKANALYST
    Name:  Analyst Gadget

 Purpose:  To find and repair problems with a disk or device.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing
           this operation.  Use 911-Recovery Mode if file corruption is
           suspected.

Keyboard:  "N"
@endnode

@node GAD_LABTEST
    Name:  Lab Test Gadget

 Purpose:  To Create/Load/Save CRC (Cyclic Redundancy Check) databases.  Used
           to compare against filesystem to check for file corruption.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "L"
@endnode

@node GAD_911
    Name:  911-Recovery Gadget

 Purpose:  To Recover data from a corrupted filesystem.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "R"
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER
    Name:  Reviver Gadget

 Purpose:  To Restore files to filesystem that have been deleted.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing this
           operation.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_LIST
    Name:  Device List Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling of device list if the list is larger than display.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Arrow Keys
@endnode

@node GAD_VOLUME
    Name:  Devices Gadget

 Purpose:  To display all devices in list.

 Warning:  If no device(s) are present, perform a scan of the SCSI bus, and use
           the 911-Recovery option to recover file(s).

Keyboard:  "D"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCSI
    Name:  SCSI Units Gadget

 Purpose:  To initiate a search of the SCSI Bus.  Will display all hard drives on
           active bus.

 Warning:  Make sure the proper SCSI device is selected.  See Device Preferences.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node MENU_QUIT
    Name:  Quit Menu

 Purpose:  To Quit/Exit the program.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "Q" or Right Amiga-Q
@endnode

@node MENU_ABOUT
    Name:  About Menu

 Purpose:  To show information about the program.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_SNAPSHOT
    Name:  SnapShot Menu

 Purpose:  To store the current position of the Ami-Back Tools window.  The
           program will be placed in this location on startup.

 Warning:  Only this only works on a Workbench screen and with Workbench 2.0+.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-N
@endnode

@node MENU_SAVE
    Name:  Save Menu

 Purpose:  To save the current program preferences to the configuration file.
           Normally used if preferences were used (but not saved when
           making selections).

           The configuration file is stored in the SYS:S directory.

           The configuration file name is Ami-BackTools.Config.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-W
@endnode

@node MENU_PALETTE
    Name:  Palette Menu

 Purpose:  To allow changing the current palette parameters.

 Warning:  This will effect the Workbench palette if the screen mode is
           set to Workbench.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-P
@endnode

@node MENU_SCREEN
    Name:  Screen Menu

 Purpose:  To allow changing/modifying the current screen characteristics.

 Warning:  This is only valid under Workbench 2.0+

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-S
@endnode

@node MENU_DEVICES
    Name:  Devices Menu

 Purpose:  To allows selecting the SCSI device to be opened during the
           find partition function.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-D
@endnode

@node MENU_SECURITY
    Name:  Security Menu

 Purpose:  To allow selecting the level of program security.  Setting the
           security level is done to prevent accidental modifications to
           any filesystem.

 Warning:  If the master password has been set, you must know it to get
           into this function.
 
Keyboard:  Right Amiga-C
@endnode

@node MENU_CACHE
    Name:  Cache Menu

 Purpose:  To allow setting up a buffer (cache) for the program to use
           during read and write operations.  This will speed up
           the program operation.

 Warning:  Only works with the General Practitioner utility.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-I
@endnode

@node MENU_GENERAL
    Name:  General Menu

 Purpose:  To allow setting the general program preferences.

 Warning:  This must be set for the files created by this program.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-G
@endnode

@node MENU_SCSI_SEARCH
    Name:  SCSI Search Menu

 Purpose:  Same as SCSI Units Gadget.

 Warning:  See SCSI Units Gadget.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_VOLUME_INFO
    Name:  Show Device Menu

 Purpose:  Same as Devices Gadget.

 Warning:  See Devices Gadget.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_RDB_SAVE
    Name:  RDBs to File Menu

 Purpose:  To save the currently select device's RDB information to an
           AmigaDOS file.

 Warning:  A SCSI bus search must be performed prior to using.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_RDB_LOAD
    Name:  File to RDB's Menu

 Purpose:  To restore RDB file information to the currently selected device.

 Warning:  MAKE SURE you have the correct file.  Restoring the incorrect
           RDB information will cause a LOSS of ALL partition information.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_GP
    Name:  General Practitioner Menu

 Purpose:  To initiate the General Practitioner Utility.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing
           this operation.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-4
@endnode

@node MENU_ANTISEPTIC
    Name:  Antiseptic Menu

 Purpose:  To initiate the Antiseptic Utility.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing
           this operation.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-6
@endnode

@node MENU_DISKANALYST
    Name:  Analyst Menu

 Purpose:  To initiate the Analyst Utility.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing
           this operation.  Use the 911-Recovery Mode if file corruption is
           suspected.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-2
@endnode

@node MENU_LABTEST
    Name:  Lab Test Menu

 Purpose:  To initiate the Lab Test Utility.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-5
@endnode

@node MENU_911
    Name:  911-Recovery Menu

 Purpose:  To initiate the 911-Recovery Utility.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-3
@endnode

@node MENU_REVIVER
    Name:  Reviver Menu

 Purpose:  To initiate the Reviver Utility.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing this
           operation.

Keyboard:  Right Amiga-1
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_SAVE
    Name:  Palette Save Gadget

 Purpose:  To Save the selected color palette parameters.

 Warning:  If using a Workbench screen, this will affect the system color palette.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_USE
    Name:  Palette Use Gadget

 Purpose:  To Use the selected color palette parameters.

 Warning:  If using a Workbench screen, this will affect the system color palette.

Keyboard:  "U"
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_CANCEL
    Name:  Palette Cancel Gadget

 Purpose:  To prevent the use of the selected palette.  This will reset to the
           palette which was used before entering palette preferences.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_PRESETS
    Name:  Palette Preset Gadget

 Purpose:  To allows selecting predefined palettes.

 Warning:  If using a Workbench screen, this will affect the system color palette.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_PALETTE
    Name:  Color Palette Gadget

 Purpose:  To allows selecting a specific color within the palette to edit.

 Warning:  If using a Workbench, screen this will affect the system color palette.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_RED_SLIDER
    Name:  Red Slide Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow editing the Red portion of the selected color.

 Warning:  If using a Workbench screen, this will affect the system color palette.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_GREEN_SLIDER
    Name:  Green Slide Gadget

 Purpose:  To allows editing the Green portion of the selected color.

 Warning:  If using a Workbench screen, this will affect the system color palette.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_BLUE_SLIDER
    Name:  Blue Slide Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow editing the Blue portion of the selected color.

 Warning:  If using a Workbench screen, this will affect the system color palette.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PALETTE_UNDO
    Name:  Undo Palette Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow you to reverse last editing of the select color palette.

 Warning:  If using a Workbench screen, this will affect the system color palette.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SCREEN_SAVE
    Name:  Save Screen Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow Saving the selected screen parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCREEN_USE
    Name:  Use Screen Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow Using the selected screen parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "U"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCREEN_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Screen Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow Canceling of the selected screen parameters.  Therefore the
           screen display will not be affected.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCREEN_TYPE
    Name:  Screen Type Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting the screen type.  The selection may be Workbench,
           Custom, or Public.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SCREEN_PUBLIC
    Name:  Public Screen Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting the option to Create or Visit a public screen.

 Warning:  If a public screen does not exist, then the gadget will be ghosted.
           Create will then be the only option available.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SCREEN_PUBNAME
    Name:  Public Screen Name Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow entering a public screen name to either Create or Visit.  If
           the Public Screen Gadget is set to Visit, you may update this gadget
           by selecting a public screen name for the list view gadget.

 Warning:  If entering a name directly into this string gadget, be sure to
           press the return key after entering the name.  Otherwise the program
           will not recognize your input.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SCREEN_DISPLAY
    Name:  Display Mode Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting the screen display mode.  Options include Interlace,
           Non-Interlace, and Clone WB.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SCREEN_LISTVIEW
    Name:  Public Screens Gadget

 Purpose:  To list the current public screens.  You will be able to select
           a screen when attempting to visit.  This list is updated each time
           you select this preference item.

 Warning:  This can only be used when Visiting a public screen.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_ABOUT_CONTINUE
    Name:  About Continue Gadget

 Purpose:  To exit About Window information.  Will exit to main program window.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_SAVE
    Name:  Save Preference Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow Saving any of the Preferences options.  Used by Security,
           Device, Disk Cache, and General Preferences.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_USE
    Name:  Use Preference Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow Using any of the Preferences options.  Used by Security,
           Device, Disk Cache, and General Preferences.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "U"
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Preference Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow Canceling Preferences items.  All selected parameters will
           be ignored and will be reset to previous settings.  Used by Security,
           Device, Disk Cache, and General Preferences.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_DEVICE
    Name:  Active Device String Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow entering the current SCSI device to be used in SCSI Search.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_LEFT
    Name:  Left Arrow Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling through the list of current system devices.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_RIGHT
    Name:  Right Arrow Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling through the list of current system devices.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_PASSWD
    Name:  Master Password String Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow entering a password to be used by the program to prevent
           accidental modifications to a device/filesystem.

 Warning:  If you forget the password see user manual on how to recover.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_SECLEVEL
    Name:  User Security Level

 Purpose:  To allow you to select the security level used by Ami-Back Tools.
           This will determine the number of requesters brought up before
           any operation that will modify the file system.  This is to
           prevent accidental modifications to a device/filesystem.

           Options range from 0 to 2.

 Warning:  A setting of 0 (zero) will result in NO notification prior to
           performing an operation that will modify the device/filesystem.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_CACHEONOFF
    Name:  Disk Caching Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow turning disk caching On/Off.  The cached is only used by
           General Practitioner during Optimizing operation.  The speed of
           the operation is dramatically improved with disk cache turned on.

 Warning:  A side-effect of using cache is that the the data is not written
           to the device as often.  Therefore if some catastrophic problem
           occurs during the operation, there is a greater possibility that
           data loss can occur.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_CACHE
    Name:  Cache Memory Gadget

 Purpose:  To indicate the amount of cache to be used for disk cache.

 Warning:  A side-effect of using cache is that the the data is not written
           to the device as often.  Therefore if some catastrophic problem
           occurs during the operation, there is a greater possibility that
           data loss can occur.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_CACHELEFT
    Name:  Cache Memory Left Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow decrementing amount of memory to use for cache.  Decrements
           are made in 64k byte blocks.

 Warning:  A side-effect of using cache is that the the data is not written
           to the device as often.  Therefore if some catastrophic problem
           occurs during the operation, there is a greater possibility that
           data loss can occur.

           The size of cache cannot exceed the largest contiguous memory block
           available.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_CACHERIGHT
    Name:  Cache Memory Right Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow incrementing amount of memory to use for cache.  Increments
           are made in 64k byte blocks.

 Warning:  A side-effect of using cache is that the the data is not written
           to the device as often.  Therefore if some catastrophic problem
           occurs during the operation, there is a greater possibility that
           data loss can occur.

           The size of cache cannot exceed the largest contiguous memory block
           available.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_DISPLAYALERT
    Name:  Display Alert Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting what type of display alert program will perform
           when an Information or Error requester is displayed.

           Options are None, Flash Only, Beep Only, or Beep and Flash.

           Under Workbench 2.0+ the beep will use the selected system sound.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_POPTOFRONT
    Name:  Pop to Front Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow you to select whether Ami-Back Tools program will pop to
           the front if an Information or Error requester is displayed.

           Options are Yes/No.

 Warning:  This will pop to the front of screen the Ami-Back Tools window is
           attached to.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_PROGRAMOPS
    Name:  Program Operations Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting Asynchronous or Synchronous IO operations used
           in 911-Recovery.  This is necessary for some machine configurations
           that will not allow high speed operations.

 Warning:  The default is Asynchronous.  Changing to Synchronous will slow
           down the IO operations.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_GENERALPATH
    Name:  General Program Path String Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow you to enter a directory path to contain files created
           by Ami-Back Tools.

 Warning:  This is only the default path.  An ASL File requester is used which
           will allow you to select the actual path.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_LOGFILEPATH
    Name:  Log File Path String Gadget

 Purpose:  To specify the FULL path to the log file used by Ami-Back Tools during
           background operations.

 Warning:  Must have FULL path.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_REQ_GENERAL
    Name:  REQ Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow the use of an ASL Requester to select the General Program
           Path.  The string gadget is automatically updated.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "R"
@endnode

@node GAD_PREFS_REQ_LOG
    Name:  REQ Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow the use of an ASL Requester to select the Log File Path
           The string gadget is automatically updated.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANALYST_START
    Name:  Analyze Device Gadget

 Purpose:  To execute the Analyst utility.  Will commence searching source
           device for problems.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing
           this operation.  Use 911-Recovery Mode if file corruption is
           suspected.

           Make sure the options Data Blocks, and Repair Action are set correctly. 

Keyboard:  "D"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANALYST_EXIT
    Name:  Exit Analyst Gadget

 Purpose:  To exit this utility and return to the Administrator.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANALYST_UNDO
    Name:  Undo Changes Gadget

 Purpose:  To undo all changes made by the Analyst to the source device.

 Warning:  If changes are undone then the errors corrected by Analyst
           will be removed.

Keyboard:  "U"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANALYST_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  To abort current Analyst operations.  You will be given option
           to continue or abort operation.

 Warning:  If operation is aborted before completing the process the filesystem
           may not be 100% error free.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANALYST_DATA
    Name:  Data Blocks Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting option to check data block integrity during Analyst
           operations.

 Warning:  If "Checked" is not selected then there is no guarantee of data
           integrity.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_ANALYST_FIX
    Name:  Repair Action Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting repair options for Analyst.  Options are Auto Repair,
           Ask Repair, or No Repair.

 Warning:  If Auto Repair is selected the Analyst will make ALL necessary repairs
           without user interaction.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_ANALYST_ERRORLIST
    Name:  Error List Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling information in Error List.  This will be necessary
           if the number of errors exceeds the display capabilities.

           You may double-click on an error to receive extra help information.
           This is only available on some error messages.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_OPTI_OPTIMIZE}
    Name:  Optimize Gadget

 Purpose:  To start the Optimizer.  Optimizes the current selected device.

 Warning:  Ensure your data is backed up (using Ami-Back) before performing
           this operation.

Keyboard:  "O"
@endnode

@node GAD_OPTI_EXIT
    Name:  Exit Gadget

 Purpose:  To exit the General Practitioner and return to the Administrator.

 Warning:  None.
 
Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_OPTI_CHECKDISK
    Name:  Check Disk Gadget

 Purpose:  To start the Check Disk function.  This will analyze the currently
           selected device for integrity prior to optimization.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_OPTI_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  To abort the Optimize or Check Disk function.  Will allow you
           verify this option.

 Warning:  Aborting the Optimizer properly through this options WILL NOT
           corrupt your filesystem.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_OPTI_OPTITYPEF
    Name:  Optimize Type F Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting File type optimization.

 Warning:  One of these types must be selected prior to start of the optimizer.
           You cannot change once the optimization process has started.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_OPTI_OPTITYPED
    Name:  Optimize Type D Gadget
    
 Purpose:  To allow selecting Directory type optimization.
 
 Warning:  One of these types must be selected prior to start of the optimizer.
           You cannot change once the optimization process has started.
 
Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_OPTI_OPTITYPEE
    Name:  Optimize Type E Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting Free Space type optimization.

 Warning:  One of these types must be selected prior to start of the optimizer.
           You cannot change once the optimization process has started.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_OPTI_DISPLAYOFF
    Name:  Graphics Display Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow turning off the graphical display during optimization.  This
           will speed up the optimization process.  This will not have a great
           effect on small partition sizes, but on large hard drives the
           speed improvement will be noticed.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_BUILD
    Name:  Build DB Gadget

 Purpose:  To start process of scanning current device.  It will build a Data
           base of the files on the device.  A CRC (Cyclic Redundancy Check)
           value it calculated for each file.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "B"
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_COMPARE
    Name:  Compare DB Gadget

 Purpose:  To start process to compare current data base against current device.
           Any errors encountered will be appropriately displayed.  See users
           manual for further description.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_EXIT
    Name:  Exit Gadget

 Purpose:  To exit Lab Test and return to The Administrator.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  To abort any process performed under Lab Test.

           Will give you the option to actually abort or continue.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_LOAD
    Name:  Load DB Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow loading a Lab Test saved Data Base.

 Warning:  The file must be of the correct format.

Keyboard:  "L"
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_SAVE
    Name:  Save DB Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow saving the current data base to an AmigaDOS file.  File is
           stored in a special data format.

 Warning:  Destination must have enough free space to hold the file.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_PRINT
    Name:  Print DB Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows printing current data base file to either the PRT: device or
           an AmigaDOS file.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "P"
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_SCROLLER_V
    Name:  Vertical Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling data base information if the number of files exceeds
           the display area.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_LAB_SCROLLER_H
    Name:  Horizontal Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling data base information if the width of the display
           exceeds the display area.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SCSI_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow aborting the partition search of the current selected drive.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_INFO_CONTINUE
    Name:  Continue Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow exiting the Device Information window.  Returns back to the
           Administrator.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_INFO_SAVEMOUNTLIST
    Name:  Save Mountlist Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow saving the current device information to a mountlist.  An ASL
           file requester will allow you to select the file location, and name.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode
	
@node GAD_LABINFO_CONTINUE
    Name:  Continue Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow exiting the Lab Test File Information window.  Will exit
           back to Lab Test.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode
	
@node GAD_R911_SEARCH
    Name:  Search Device Gadget

 Purpose:  To start 911-Recovery scan.  Will search the current device and build
           a file display.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_RECOVER
    Name:  Recover Data Gadget

 Purpose:  After tagging file(s) to be recovered selecting this gadget will bring
           up the Recovery display, allowing the parameters to be used during
           the recovery.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "R"
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  To abort the 911-Recovery scan.  Will allow you to verify the
           abort operation.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_EXIT
    Name:  Exit Gadget

 Purpose:  To exit 911-Recovery Utility and Return to the Administrator.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_SCROLL_V
    Name:  Vertical Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling of file information if the number of files exceeds
           the display area.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_SCROLL_H
    Name:  Horizontal Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling of file information if the width of the display
           exceeds the display area.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_MODE
    Name:  911-Recovery Mode Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting the 911-Recovery Mode.

           Options are Recovery and Restore.

 Warning:  Restore mode will ONLY restore files recovered by Ami-Back Tools.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_RESTORE
    Name:  Restore Data Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow restoring previously recovered (to floppy) data to a device.

 Warning:  Data must have been recovered using Ami-Back Tools.

Keyboard:  "D"
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_START_RECOVERY
    Name:  Start Recovery Gadget

 Purpose:  To start recovery of selected files.

 Warning:  Make sure you have the destination device set correctly before beginning
           this operation.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_START_RESTORE
    Name:  Restore Data Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow continuing to Restore Display where parameters will be
           displayed for Restore of data.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "T"
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_DESTINATION
    Name:  Destination String Gadget

 Purpose:  To specify a destination string used for Recovery.

 Warning:  Must be a device or directory.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_COMPRESSION
    Name:  Compression Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow turning On/Off compression when recovering to floppy drive(s).

 Warning:  The recovery time will increase when using compression.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_DESTSTRING
    Name:  Destination String Gadget

 Purpose:  To specify a destination string used for Restore.

 Warning:  Must be a device or directory.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_R911_START_RESTORE2
    Name:  Start Restore Gadget

 Purpose:  To start restore of selected files.

 Warning:  Make sure you have the destination device set correctly before beginning
           this operation.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANALYSTHELP_CONTINUE
    Name:  Continue Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow exiting Analyst Help.  Returns to Analyst screen.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER_EXIT
    Name:  Exit Gadget

 Purpose:  To exit Reviver and return to the Administrator.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER_SEARCH
    Name:  Search Device Gadget

 Purpose:  To start search of current source device for undeleted files.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER_REVIVE
    Name:  Revive Data Gadget

 Purpose:  To start process to Revive (Undelete) files.

 Warning:  Make sure you have the two options Dup. File Detect, and File
           Unrecoverable set to your preferences prior to starting
           this function.

Keyboard:  "R"
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  To abort Reviver Search, or Revive function.  Will be able to verify
           the abort.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER_SCROLL_V
    Name:  Vertical Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling of file information if the number of files exceeds
           the display area.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER_SCROLL_H
    Name:  Horizontal Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow scrolling of file information if the width of the display
           exceeds the display area.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER_DUPFILE
    Name:  Dup. File Detect Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting options of "Ask User", and "Auto Skip" if a
           duplicate file has been detected during the Reviving process.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_REVIVER_NORECOVER
    Name:  File Unrecoverable Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting options of "Notify User", and "Auto Skip" if a
           file that is not recoverable is detected.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_ANTI_EXIT}
    Name:  Exit Gadget

 Purpose:  To exit Antiseptic and return to the Administrator.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANTI_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  To abort the Wipe function once started.  Will allow you to verify
           the abort.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANTI_WIPE
    Name:  Wipe Gadget

 Purpose:  To start the Wipe procedure.

 Warning:  Make sure you check the CORRECT device, and Antiseptic Type before
           initiating this operation.

           Once a device/free space is wiped you may NOT recover any data
           from the affected area.

Keyboard:  "W"
@endnode

@node GAD_ANTI_TYPE
    Name:  Antiseptic Type

 Purpose:  To allow selecting options "Free Space" or "Device"

 Warning:  If DEVICE option is selected the ENTIRE device will be WIPED of ALL
           data.  You will not be able to recover any lost data.  Unless it
           has been backed up (using Ami-Back.)

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_ANTI_PASSES
    Name:  Number Passes Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow selecting number of passes Antiseptic will use to Wipe
           data from current device.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RDB_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  To allow aborting RDBs to File, or File to RDBs execution.

 Warning:  During RDBs to File the AmigaDOS file created will be removed if
           the process is aborted.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode
